Douglas



As regards the skidmobile, is it too wide for riding in a lane of traffic? How fast can it be  ridden? Can it be locked in place (upright) if parked in a space at the store? Will it lock onto the scooter to make stealing the whole rig pure hell for potential miscreants? Seems to be better than a trike (other than MP3) as it allows leans while still riding like a real mtrcycle.






Tom Roderick



Skidbike is a tool used in a closed course environment for training purposes. It is not meant to be ridden on pubic roads.






Douglas



(Um, Tom….I knew that, I wuz bein’ cute….I thought)








Old MOron



I like your outside-the-box thinking. It would be cool if this could be used for convenience and safety in day-to-day riding. But it would be difficult-to-impossible to pull off.
Imagine hitting bumps or potholes. The bike has suspension that is carefully engineered to deal with that situation. But the Skidbike apparatus would be a whole lot of unsprung weight flopping about, far away from the motorcycle’s center of gravity.






